commitResults.messageTitle: Completed: Level 1. Greet, Echo, Exit added personality features for chatbot Duke for better audience engagement
Revert "Completed: Level 1. Greet, Echo, Exit"
Completed Level 1: Greet, Echo, Exit. Added features of personality/emotion, and accepts user input of entire lines rather than a single String of one word.
edited for cleanliness

Completed Level 2: Add, List Output is now more appealing and easier to discern. Added some comments for easy development. Further consideration for encapsulation added. Reworked formatting of output.
Updated TaskHandler file: added addTaskToStored message for better code cleanliness and better scope.

Completed Level 3: Mark as Done. Added more helper functions in Task.java and TaskHandler.java. Tasks now have a isDone attribute, which can be marked as true/false. The Task obtainStatusIcon String value depends on the value of isDone. Tasks can be marked as complete using doTask method in Task.java. Added more cases in TaskHandler's switch-case block.
Edited for better user engagement. Improved formatting, and chatbot emotion.

Completed Level 4: ToDos, Events, Deadlines Task is now an abstract class, which ToDo, Event, Deadline are child classes with overridden methods toString and taskAddedMessage. Added more user-engaging features in TaskHandler to improve user experience. ToDo, Event, Deadline Tasks have their own unique responses. Improved code cleanliness. Created packages and JavaDocs as there are now sufficent number of classes to have distinct, clearly observable differences, and to make code neater, and more understandable.
minor bug fixes in greetings
misc changes, playing around to learn about how to use .bat files

Completed A-TextUiTesting: Automated Text UI Testing. Removed packaging to simplify code. Packages will probably be added later. runtest.bat runs successfully and correctly, with no differences detected between actual and expected output.

Completed Level 5: Handle Errors. Changed the if-else conditional printing statements to match those of the appropriate Exceptions. All Exceptions in this program are DukeExceptions (parent class). These 7 Exceptions are: DukeException, AlreadyDoneException, InputUnclearException, EmptyTaskListException, ToDoException, DeadlineException, EventException.
Added javadoc comments for the 7 Exceptions
some minor spacing edits

Completed Level 6: Delete. Provided a deleteTask(command) method to delete the task from a given command (raw String text) to which actual command (based on the int value given) represent the index+1 in the ArrayList collection. Created an 8th Exception, DeleteException, and its corresponding method for printing along with horizontal formatting lines.
Added Task name and time limit/duration (if applicable) for delete user commands.

Completed Level 7: Save. Now creates a file if not previously existing and updates if whenever a change is made to the overall Task List. Task done status is updated accordingly as with icons. Reopening Duke will load this file, such that there is a 'memory' attached to it.

Completed Level-8: Dates & Times. Added restrictions to how Deadline limit and Event time are to be presented as input to Duke. Failure for such restrictions prompts user a reminder on the limit/time format. Outputs limit/time in a specific MMM d yyyy format.
Completed A-MoreOOP.
commitResults.messageBody:
Fixed some bugs where the type of Task was reflected wrongly.

Added classes into packages, namely packages: exceptions, tasks (as they were very similar and had similar functions).

Reworked previous classes to suit the Task Requirements, requiring major shifting of code and refactoring.
Ui: deals with interactions with the user
Storage: deals with loading tasks from the file and saving tasks in the file
Parser: deals with making sense of the user command
TaskList: contains the task list e.g., it has operations to add/delete tasks in the list

Conducted further developer testing.

commitResults.messageTitle: Completed A-Packages. Achieved the Minimal: put all classes in one package e.g., duke Achieved also the Stretch goal: divide into multiple packages as the number of classes increase.
commitResults.messageBody:
Essentially I have already done the work previously, and this commit simply adds my previous packaging efforts into one large package: duke.
Using IntelliJ features, this was very smoothly done.

Improved find method in TaskList. Users can now search for words of longer than length 1.
